# Deny-all, then allow only what the Lambda image actually needs.
# The CDK IngestStack passes REPO_ROOT as the Docker asset directory, so
# without this file CDK hashes (and Docker uploads) tens of GB of cached
# API JSONs, git history, cdk.out/, artefacts/, etc. before the build
# even starts. See infrastructure/stacks/ingest_stack.py.
**

!Dockerfile.lambda
!requirements.lambda.txt
!src/**

# Within src/, still drop Python caches — they bloat the image and
# change on every local run, defeating the asset-hash cache.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
